liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: This is a famous victory over the co-hosts for the World Cup debutants, and an absolute cat among the pigeons in Group A. The Philippines have their first win at their first World Cup with their first goal from their first shot on goal. Ain't that somethin'.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: The Philippines score a stunning 1-0 upset over New Zealand!

children.content: This is a famous victory over the co-hosts for the World Cup debutants, and an absolute cat among the pigeons in Group A.
The Philippines have their first win at their first World Cup with their first goal from their first shot on goal. Ain't that somethin'.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: VAR was always going to have something to say, because there were fine margins all over the place, and they've said Hannah Wilkinson was offside on her run for Ali Riley's long ball. It's such a shame because she did brilliantly well after it, shepherding the ball until it was about 90 per cent of the way over the byline, then turning back and chipping perfectly for Jacqui Hand to nod in expertly. The offside call was VERY tight, but probably right? I don't know. It's hard to tell for sure from the angles we've seen. Even in the 3D modelling it's basically impossible to see. Must be millimetres in it.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 70' NEW ZEALAND'S EQUALISER IS DISALLOWED!

children.content: VAR was always going to have something to say, because there were fine margins all over the place, and they've said Hannah Wilkinson was offside on her run for Ali Riley's long ball.

It's such a shame because she did brilliantly well after it, shepherding the ball until it was about 90 per cent of the way over the byline, then turning back and chipping perfectly for Jacqui Hand to nod in expertly.
The offside call was VERY tight, but probably right? I don't know. It's hard to tell for sure from the angles we've seen.
Even in the 3D modelling it's basically impossible to see. Must be millimetres in it.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Another upset is on the cards in Group A, with the World Cup debutants in the lead against the tournament co-hosts. All the talk before the game was about how the Football Ferns could just about lock up a knockout spot with a win this afternoon, but suddenly the Philippines have thrown that into disarray. Sarina Bolden's goal was the result of near-perfect attacking play from Philippines, with Sara Eggesvik's cross put perfectly in her path and the leap and header was clean. New Zealand will be disappointed by the efforts of defenders CJ Bott and Rebekah Stott, while goalie Victoria Esson got both hands to it right in front of her face but couldn't handle. New Zealand beat Norway in their opener, and now if this game stays like this, the group is completely wide open. Especially if Norway beat Switzerland tonight, then every team in the group will be on one win each!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: Philippines lead 1-0 New Zealand at the break
